 **Brotato** - I am usually not a fan of similar roguelikes, because you can win with just skill, but in this case it feels like having a good build matters.
 **Polytopia** - 4x game that I actually finish the games of, and they are really quick, as whole thing about the game is that it is very simple and quick.
 **SUPERHOT**  - I don't even remember why I bought these games, but it was nice to play a game that actually has an end point, also is a pretty fun pseudo puzzle game.
 Some honorable mentions to **Luck be a Landlord**, and **Dorfromantik**, which I like to play when watching stuff.
 And final mention I am quite often thinking about playing **Minecraft BtA**, mainly due to the fact that it has some heavy nostalgia factors for me, and I no longer enjoy the modern game.
